Finmeccanica, RWE, Veolia Environnement: European Equity Preview

-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-12-06T05:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/finmeccanica-rwe-veolia-environnement-european-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  rose 0.8 percent to 242.75. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  increased 0.6 percent to 2,324.78. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, gained
1.2 percent to 2,369.39.  Finmeccanica Spa (FNC)  : Italy’s biggest defense company
had its long-term  credit rating  cut to BBB- with a “negative
outlook” from BBB by  Standard & Poor’s , which cited lower
earnings and restructuring of some of its divisions. The stock
rose 9.8 percent to 3.56 euros.  RWE AG (RWE)  :  Germany’s second-largest utility company
is seeking to raise about 2.1 billion euros ($2.8 billion) to
cut debt by selling 80.4 million shares at 26 euros to 27.5
euros, according to a term sheet obtained by Bloomberg News. The
stock fell 5.1 percent to 28.35 euros.  UBS AG (UBSN)  : Switzerland’s largest bank and Citigroup
Inc. are marketing $673.9 million of bonds backed by commercial
mortgages, as banks clear their books of stockpiled loans. The
stock added 0.4 percent to 11.4 francs.  Veolia Environnement SA (VIE)  : The Paris-based utility
company will unveil tomorrow plans to “disengage” from its 50
percent holding in Veolia Transport, Le Figaro reported, without
citing anyone. The stock advanced 1.2 percent to 9.52 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inyoung Hwang in New York at 
 ihwang7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net . 